*INV1:	&-um now this next thing we hafta do +...
%mor:	adv|now det|this-Def-Dem-Sing adj|next-S1 noun|thing-Ger pron|we-Prs-Nom-P1 aux|hafta-Fin-Ind-Pres-P1 verb|do-Fin-Ind-Pres-P1 +...
%gra:	1|4|ADVMOD 2|4|DET 3|4|AMOD 4|0|ROOT 5|7|NSUBJ 6|7|AUX 7|4|ACL-RELCL 8|4|PUNCT
@Comment:	Dear Tom I Miss you How is Alex? How is Paula? Amy Love
@Comment:	Chi decides to write the letter to her uncle Tom. Mot tells Chi to write Dear uncle Tom. Mot does a lot of sounding out words to help Chi spell them. Mot is patient and kind to Chi. Chi's younger brother occasionally speaks to Mot , but Mot tries to concentrate on Chi. It seems that most of the ideas about what to write come from Mot. Mot is concerned about question marks but no other form of punctuation. Chi has nice penmenship. There is no punctuation other then the two question marks. <I miss you> is on a different line than <Dear Tom> but is not indented. Amy Love is not indented either. Chi refuses to read back the letter , and EXP doesn't insist.
